org.numenta.nupic.util

Class AbstractSparseMatrix<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.numenta.nupic.util.AbstractFlatMatrix<T>
      • org.numenta.nupic.util.AbstractSparseMatrix<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, FlatMatrix<T>, Matrix<T>, SparseMatrix<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractSparseBinaryMatrix, SetSparseMatrix, SparseObjectMatrix

    public abstract class AbstractSparseMatrix<T>
extends AbstractFlatMatrix<T>
implements SparseMatrix<T>, java.io.Serializable
    Allows storage of array data in sparse form, meaning that the indexes of the data stored are maintained while empty indexes are not. This allows savings in memory and computational efficiency because iterative algorithms need only query indexes containing valid data. The dimensions of matrix defined at construction time and immutable - matrix fixed size data structure.
    Author:
    David Ray, Jose Luis Martin

    Serialized Form
